	   <tr><td colspan=2>That has nothing to do with luck. Most of these have another char at L60 or around that pays for the lambent. These guys have usually played for years and worked hard to get there.<br><br>On the other hand, these guys miss out on a lot. A low level bard in full lambent with a good weapon can take on yellows or reds with minor or no downtime and level incredibly fast. You miss most of the fun playing at lower levels.<br><br>There is a huge shortage of bards at higher levels. They are needed on raids because of the huge resist buffs they can provide. So a lot of guilds PL bards up to L50+ in a few days. These bards are tools, no more.<br><br>So, why be envious of other people equipment? Is they wouldn't have it, would that make you a better bard?<br><br>If you detest other people twinking, FV is the server to be on. Since everyone has just one char, there is little twinking around.<br>&nbsp;<br>Nindor<br>L52 Dwarven Cleric on Zebuxoruk</td></tr>
